    I think this hotel is the poor attempt to renovate a ryad. It had two wings, the second one looked good and well decorated, but I got to stay in the first wing. As a student in architecture, some things shocked me in this place. Stair steps 
    I think this hotel is the poor attempt to renovate a ryad. It had two wings, the second one looked good and well decorated, but I got to stay in the first wing. As a student in architecture, some things shocked me in this place. Stair steps around 30 cm of height, small rooms without bathrooms and a common bathroom for the upper floor that cannot be cleaned frequently enough. A room in the lower floor with which the bathroom is only separared by a low wall and a curtain, because the bathroom had no window, a huge problem if you need to poop. The room decor is really poor and the space organization feels improvised, the plumbing needs to be fixed and the cleaning improved. Worst hotel/ryad I've ever been to, no respect of the basic architectural norms. The only thing I enjoyed was the patio, the location near the marina, and the really nice and caring staff.

    About this hotel

    A 12-minute walk from the Tangier American Legation Institute for Moroccan Studies, this laid-back hotel in an airy 19th-century building is 2 km from museums in the 17th-century Dar-el-Makhzen palace.

    Simple rooms with Moorish design touches offer Wi-Fi, satellite TV and desks. Suites add sitting rooms with fireplaces.

    Breakfast is served in an open-air lounge/dining area or on a leafy garden terrace.

    Check-in time: 2:00 PM
    Check-out time: 12:00 PM
